metadata.name: El Ollin
metadata.description:
Nahui Ollin has been described as "the sun (Tōnatiuh) in its four movements. 

"When the fourth sun ended, Nahui Ollin emerged "from the remnant matter of an earlier age of humanity."​

What is Old is New and what is New has been Old. We are who we have been and will continue after those of us here right now, are no more. 

My interpretation of the Ancient Myths and Mythology of the Aztec (Mexica People) is focused on the symbolism with a modern twist of color.
